      "content": "While taking simvastatin a few hours apart might not cause significant harm, it's still not the ideal solution. Taking statins at a variable time can affect their efficacy and may lead to inconsistency in their blood levels. However, in this case, taking your simvastatin a few hours after clarithromycin and waiting 3-4 hours before taking the next clarithromycin dose might not be significantly worse.",
